prompts.title: Maintaining results and feeling safe in freedom
questions: What part of me still believes freedom means I'll lose control?
What would it look like to feel safe being this version of me long term?
When I catch myself tightening up around food or my body, what emotions am I really trying to control?
What does my nervous system expect to happen when things are 'good'?
What stories from my past tell me I can't trust myself?
What would it feel like to let my body lead for once?
If I didn't have to earn this peace, how would I show up around food and my body today?
Where am I still trying to prove I can 'keep it off'?
What does sustainable success actually feel like in my body, not look like on paper?
How can I create evidence that I am safe here?
